The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge have embarked on the second leg of their Caribbean tour which has taken them from Belize to Jamaica. Kate was seeing delivering a speech at Shortwood Teacher College, hailing the “crucial” role of teachers “at the front line ”in shaping the early years. She continued: “We are on the cusp of one of the biggest opportunities for positive change in generations.” In an emotional address, the Duchess revealed that since their arrival in Jamaica, she had "been touched by the warmth this island has shown us." THIS LIVE BLOG HAS NOW CLOSED. 